## D5. Runtime staging byte/line limits (7 MAX_DIRECT_GRID_* constants pinned in manifest)
# NOTE: MAX_PACKAGE_MANIFEST_BYTES is a non-direct-grid PRCP-manifest cap and is
# EXPLICITLY EXCLUDED from the 7-constant pinned set per manifest scope.
# runtime.py:52-58 constants are code-pinned (no runtime env override in the current
# runtime.py shape) — 'runtime_effective' below equals the manifest pin unless the
# code has drifted since manifest freeze.
#   MAX_DIRECT_GRID_TSD_FORC_BYTES         pinned=      8,388,608 bytes/lines (from manifest, per runtime.py:52-58)
#   MAX_DIRECT_GRID_FORCING_CSV_BYTES      pinned=      8,388,608 bytes/lines (from manifest, per runtime.py:52-58)
#   MAX_DIRECT_GRID_SP_ATT_BYTES           pinned=     33,554,432 bytes/lines (from manifest, per runtime.py:52-58)
#   MAX_DIRECT_GRID_TSD_FORC_LINES         pinned=        250,000 bytes/lines (from manifest, per runtime.py:52-58)
#   MAX_DIRECT_GRID_FORCING_CSV_LINES      pinned=        250,000 bytes/lines (from manifest, per runtime.py:52-58)
#   MAX_DIRECT_GRID_SP_ATT_LINES           pinned=      2,000,000 bytes/lines (from manifest, per runtime.py:52-58)
#   MAX_DIRECT_GRID_STAGING_LINE_BYTES     pinned=         65,536 bytes/lines (from manifest, per runtime.py:52-58)
# all 7 staging limits are positive integers; manifest not corrupt

# D5' Audit-chain rationale (why manifest-pinned staging values equal the deployed values
#      without an on-node runtime file read):
#   (a) workers/shud_runtime/runtime.py:52-58 constants are plain integer literals with no
#       env override (grep for _env_int / os.getenv in that block returns 0 matches — the
#       env override wiring only exists on the producer side, workers/forcing_producer/producer.py:318-324).
#   (b) Tree-equivalence attest (binder header line 19) binds baseline↔carrier zero diff on
#       `workers/`, so the deployed runtime.py bytes at capture time equal the baseline_commit
#       runtime.py bytes.
#   (c) The readiness-manifest.v1.json companion .sha256 is verified at driver start; if the
#       manifest bytes had drifted the driver would have failed at _load_manifest before D1.
#   (d) node-27 `git pull --ff-only` discipline sets the deployed working tree file bytes to
#       the code-carrier commit's tree, which the tree-equivalence attest in (b) proves is
#       identical to the baseline_commit tree for `workers/`.
#   Therefore the runtime constants deployed at capture time = manifest-pinned values, by
#   transitive derivation. Contrast with D4 producer limits which DO have env override wiring
#   (_env_int in producer.py) and thus require the runtime os.environ read + grep-c capture
#   above; runtime.py has no such wiring, so a runtime file read adds nothing over the chain.

